                    Medical Informatics Training Program

   The Lister Hill National Center for Biomedical Communications (LHNCBC)
       conducts a Medical Informatics Training Program to provide support
       for visiting scientists and students for research participation at
       the Center for visits ranging from a few months to one or more
       years. Research and training programs include:


     * Postdoctoral Research

     * Training for Graduate and Medical Students

     * Training for College Students

     * Research Program for Visiting Faculty

     * Clinical Elective for Medical and Dental Students

     * NLM Rotation for Medical Informatics Trainees

     This is an equal opportunity program open to all qualified persons
     without regard to race, sex, sexual orientation, religion, age,
     color disability or national origin.
